The paper deals with computational mechanism design and game theory, which are central topics in cs.GT (Game Theory and Economics). The focus is on Sponsored Search Auctions (SSAs), which are a type of information retrieval system, making cs.IR (Information Retrieval) another likely sub-category. The paper also discusses algorithms for finding optimal allocations, which could fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper uses mathematical models to analyze the efficiency of different auction mechanisms, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning).
